<title>
‚ÄòMaintainable Code Is More Important Than Clever Code‚Äô
</title>
<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://blog.dropbox.com/topics/company/thank-you--guido"/>
<link rel="shorturl" type="text/html" href="http://df4.us/rxz"/>
<link rel="related" type="text/html" href="https://daringfireball.net/linked/2019/11/01/van-rossum-clever-code"/>
<id>tag:daringfireball.net,2019:/linked//6.36215</id>
<published>2019-11-01T20:33:09Z</published>
<updated>2019-11-01T20:33:10Z</updated>
<author>
<name>John Gruber</name>
<uri>http://daringfireball.net/</uri>
</author>
<content type="html" xml:base="https://daringfireball.net/linked/" xml:lang="en">
<![CDATA[
<p>The Dropbox company blog, giving thanks to Python creator Guido van Rossum:</p> <blockquote> <p>‚ÄúThere was a small number of really smart, really young coders who produced a lot of very clever code that only they could understand,‚Äù said van Rossum. ‚ÄúThat is probably the right attitude to have when you‚Äôre a really small startup.‚Äù</p> <p>But as the company grew, new engineers who joined couldn‚Äôt understand the code. Clever code is usually short and cryptic, written by and for the individual who came up with it, but is hard for anyone else to understand‚Äâ‚Äî‚Äâand nearly impossible to maintain. Guido called this ‚Äúcowboy coding culture‚Äù. He recognized its value in our early stages of trying to implement things quickly, but knew it wouldn‚Äôt be sustainable over time, so he decided to speak up in his own quiet way.</p> <p>‚ÄúWhen asked, I would give people my opinion that maintainable code is more important than clever code,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúIf I encountered clever code that was particularly cryptic, and I had to do some maintenance on it, I would probably rewrite it. So I led by example, and also by talking to other people.‚Äù</p> </blockquote> <p>My very favorite quote along these lines <a href="https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Brian_Kernighan">is from Brian Kernighan</a>: ‚ÄúEveryone knows that debugging is twice as hard as writing a program in the first place. So if you‚Äôre as clever as you can be when you write it, how will you ever debug it?‚Äù</p> <div> <a title="Permanent link to ‚Äò‚ÄòMaintainable Code Is More Important Than Clever Code‚Äô‚Äô" href="https://daringfireball.net/linked/2019/11/01/van-rossum-clever-code">&nbsp;‚òÖ&nbsp;</a> </div>
]]>
</content>
